MIRROR TREE

You are given a binary tree. Your task is to check whether the tree is structurally symmetric around its center.

A binary tree is said to be symmetric if the left subtree is a mirror image of the right subtree.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer N
N is the number of nodes in the binary tree

The next (N - 1) lines describe the edges of the tree
Each line contains three values:
pi ci Ri

where
pi is the parent node value
ci is the child node value
Ri represents the relationship
L means ci is the left child of pi
R means ci is the right child of pi

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print YES if the binary tree is symmetric
Print NO if the binary tree is not symmetric

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ N ≤ 10000
1 ≤ pi, ci ≤ 100000
Ri is either L or R
All node values are distinct
No duplicate edges are given

SAMPLE INPUT

7
1 2 L
1 3 R
3 4 L
3 5 R
2 6 R
2 7 L

SAMPLE OUTPUT

YES

EXPLANATION

The left subtree and right subtree are mirror images of each other, so the tree is symmetric.





private static boolean isMirror(Node left, Node right) {
    if(left==null&&right==null) return true;
    if(left==null||right==null) return false;
    return isMirror(right.right,left.left)&&isMirror(right.left,left.right);
  
}

private static void isMirrorTree(Node root) {
    if(root==null){
    System.out.println("YES");
    return;
    }
    boolean check=isMirror(root.left,root.right);
    if(check)
    {
        System.out.println("YES");
    }
    else{
        System.out.println("NO");
    }
}




